Description:
HOT PROPERTY IN TIMBERTOP
"One of the hottest properties to hit the Timbertop market."
In a stunning location in Officer's premier estate the property is impeccably positioned. Within walking distance to what will be Officer's newest primary school and close to both the Beaconsfield and Officer primary strip of shops. It's also walking distance to public transport and parkland which is central to the welcoming Timbertop community.
The house is a majestic, family-friendly house. The Carlisle-built, 31 square house is only a few years old and importantly it's north-facing.
Featuring:
- 4 bedrooms, the large master with walk-in robe and en-suite;
- Lounge room;
- Rumpus room currently being used as a gym;
- Open plan living/dining room that includes fire place;
- Modern kitchen with stone bench tops and walk-in pantry;
- Alfresco with decking that spills over into the incredibly maintained backyard;
- Double car garage with remote access;
- Heating and cooling.
This is a MUST for anyone looking for their perfect upgrade.
Ray White prides itself on being as accurate as possible however anyone considering purchasing the property should undertake their own due diligence to confirm the above.
